<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9FEF5CFF12F9B7FE03F9DC" blockId="55.[151,1436,1538,1637]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
This tribe is known for the Neotropical and Ethiopic Regions, encompassing 51 genera and 226 recognized species, with 21 genera and 53 species currently recorded for 
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFF9FEF5CFD75F993FC8DF9F8" box="[752,824,1574,1600]" name="Brazil" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. We recorded two species of two genera of the tribe at the Iguaçu National Park.
</paragraph>
